description:
Under certain circumstances code assist eats too much code.

Consider the enclosed class. As a programmer, I must add a parameter to the baz call in bar to make the program correct.

Steps:
1. Execute the following code:

   public class X {
      void bar(X x) {
         baz(x.foo());
      }
      int foo() {
         return 5;
      }
      void baz(int i, int j) {
      }
   }

2. Observe the code completion behavior.

Expected Behavior:

The code should be changed to:

   baz(x.foo()x.foo())

Actual Behavior:

The code is changed to:

   baz(x.foo().foo())

SR:
1. Execute the following code:

   public class X {
      void bar(X x) {
         baz(x.foo());
      }
      int foo() {
         return 5;
      }
      void baz(int i, int j) {
      }
   }

2. Observe the code completion behavior. The code should be changed to baz(x.foo()x.foo()) instead of baz(x.foo().foo())
